[I] Statically typed embeddable scripting language

[T] Umka is a statically typed embeddable scripting language. It combines the
[T] simplicity and flexibility needed for scripting with a compile-time
[T] protection against type errors.

[U] https://github.com/vtereshkov/umka-lang

[A] Vasiliy Tereshkov
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

[C] extra/development

[L] BSD
[V] 1.5.6

[D] 1ac8cac63227f03f06e234cd4692951e29ec533480f3a1981eff7e47 umka-lang-1.5.6.tar.gz https://github.com/vtereshkov/umka-lang/archive/refs/tags/v1.5.6/

makeinstopt=
hook_add postmake 5 "cp build/include/* $root$includedir"
hook_add postmake 5 "cp build/{*.a,*.so} $root$libdir"
hook_add postmake 5 "cp build/umka $root$bindir"
